cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LLM Phishing-Vulnerability Bias Audit"
message: "If you use this dataset, code, or findings, please cite this repository."
type: software
authors:
  - alias: "jujuliaa12"
abstract: >-
  A multi-provider empirical study of demographic bias in open-source LLMs when
  asked to assess phishing vulnerability. 855 persona records across 14 model-
  provider configurations from 5 inference providers, evaluated with chi-square,
  Welch's t-tests, Fisher's exact tests, Detoxify, and qualitative coding. The
  study finds that bias is implicit (toxicity is near zero) but statistically
  highly significant under forced-choice probing.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - bias audit
  - phishing
  - cybersecurity
  - DECODINGTRUST
  - fairness
  - trustworthy ML
license: MIT
